'''DTU Nanotech''' (before 2008 called '''MIC•DTU''') is a [[research institute]] of [[microtechnology|micro-]] and [[nanotechnology]] at the [[Technical University of Denmark]] (DTU) in Kongens Lyngby, {{convert|10|km|mi}} north of [[Copenhagen]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.nanotech.dtu.dk/english/About-NTCH | title=About Us | publisher=DTU Nanotech | date=12 November 2015 | accessdate=7 January 2016 | author=Jørgensen, Tine Elkjær}}</ref>

DTU Nanotech represents a research environment where micro and nanotechnology are applied to a wide range of scientific disciplines, e.g. [[mechanics]], [[optics]], [[chemistry]], and the [[life sciences]]. 

DTU Nanotech hosts more than 100 research projects with access to [[cleanroom]] facilities, chemical laboratories, biochemical laboratories, and optical laboratories. DTU Nanotech is the main user of [[DTU Cen]], state of the art center for [[electron microscopy]], and of [[DTU Danchip]], state of the art cleanroom on a global level. 

